en_318696_0	Minister John Amaratunga says an extensive investigation will be conducted to inquire about the incident of the death of seven wild elephants.
en_318696_1	Addressing a media briefing held in Colombo, the Minister said that interim report of the investigation has already been received by him.
en_318696_2	Minister Amaratunga expressed his regret over the incident and stated that no such devastating incident pertaining to wild life in the country was reported previously.
en_318696_3	The Minister also said that only after the reception of the final report, cause of the incident can be declared.
